---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
import AdSlot from '../../components/AdSlot.astro';
import siteConfig from '../../data/site-config.json';
import blogPosts from '../../data/blog-posts.json';

const post = blogPosts.find(p => p.slug === 'porta-potty-backyard-party')!;
const siteUrl = `https://${siteConfig.domain}`;

const articleData = {
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  datePublished: post.publishedAt,
  dateModified: post.updatedAt,
  author: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: post.author.name,
    description: post.author.bio
  },
  publisher: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: siteConfig.name,
    logo: { '@type': 'ImageObject', url: `${siteUrl}/images/PottyDirectory_Logo.png` }
  },
  mainEntityOfPage: { '@type': 'WebPage', '@id': `${siteUrl}/blog/${post.slug}` }
};

const relatedPosts = blogPosts.filter(p => p.slug !== post.slug).slice(0, 3);
---

<BaseLayout title={post.title} description={post.description}>
  <StructuredData type="Article" data={articleData} />

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
    <nav class="mb-8">
      <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-gray-500">
        <li><a href="/" class="hover:text-primary-600">Home</a></li>
        <li>/</li>
        <li><a href="/blog" class="hover:text-primary-600">Blog</a></li>
        <li>/</li>
        <li class="text-gray-900">Backyard Party</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-10">
      <span class="inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-700 text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full mb-4">Events</span>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 leading-tight">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">{post.description}</p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-primary-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold text-lg">PP</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-gray-900">{post.author.name}</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">{post.readTime} • Updated December 2024</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

      <p>
        Backyard parties are the best. Graduation celebrations, birthday bashes, family reunions, summer cookouts - there's nothing quite like hosting in your own space. But when you're inviting 30, 50, or 100+ guests, your house's single bathroom suddenly becomes a bottleneck.
      </p>

      <p>
        That's where renting a porta potty makes sense. It keeps lines short, protects your home's plumbing, and means guests don't have to traipse through your living room every time nature calls. Let me walk you through everything you need to know.
      </p>

      <AdSlot slot="content" />

      <h2 id="do-you-need-one">Do You Actually Need a Porta Potty?</h2>

      <p>
        Here's a quick gut check:
      </p>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6 my-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-800 mb-2">Yes, Get a Porta Potty If:</h4>
        <ul class="text-green-700 space-y-1">
          <li>You're hosting 35+ guests</li>
          <li>The party is 4+ hours long</li>
          <li>Alcohol is being served (more bathroom trips)</li>
          <li>Your home has only one bathroom</li>
          <li>You don't want guests inside your house</li>
          <li>It's a kids' party (they can't wait!)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 my-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Probably Don't Need One If:</h4>
        <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-1">
          <li>Under 25 guests for a few hours</li>
          <li>You have 2+ easily accessible bathrooms</li>
          <li>It's a short event (2-3 hours)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 id="how-many">How Many Porta Potties Do You Need?</h2>

      <p>
        For backyard parties, use this simple formula:
      </p>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-xl p-6 my-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Quick Calculator</h4>
        <ul class="text-blue-800 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Up to 50 guests:</strong> 1 unit</li>
          <li><strong>50-100 guests:</strong> 2 units</li>
          <li><strong>100-150 guests:</strong> 3 units</li>
          <li><strong>150-200 guests:</strong> 4 units</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-blue-700 mt-4 text-sm">Add 1 extra unit if serving alcohol. Add 1 ADA unit if guests include elderly or disabled individuals.</p>
      </div>

      <p>
        For most backyard parties with 40-75 guests, a single unit is fine. If you're pushing over 75-100, get two - lines move faster and guests won't be crossing their legs waiting.
      </p>

      <h2 id="what-type">What Type of Unit Should You Get?</h2>

      <h3>Standard Porta Potty</h3>
      <p>
        The classic blue (or gray/green) unit with a toilet, toilet paper, and hand sanitizer. Perfectly adequate for casual parties.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $100-175 for a weekend</p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Casual cookouts, kids' parties, budget-conscious hosts</p>

      <h3>Deluxe Unit with Hand Wash Station</h3>
      <p>
        Includes a small sink with running water and soap - a nice touch that guests appreciate.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $150-250 for a weekend</p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Longer parties, food-heavy events, more discerning guests</p>

      <h3>Flushable/VIP Unit</h3>
      <p>
        A step up with a flushing toilet, better ventilation, and often a mirror. Feels more like a real bathroom.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $200-350 for a weekend</p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Graduation parties, milestone birthdays, upscale BBQs</p>

      <h3>Restroom Trailer</h3>
      <p>
        A mobile bathroom with multiple stalls, AC, running water, and real fixtures. Basically a bathroom on wheels.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $500-1,500+ for a weekend</p>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Weddings, formal events, large gatherings where comfort matters</p>

      <h2 id="placement">Where to Put It</h2>

      <p>
        Location matters for both convenience and keeping things pleasant:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Away from food areas:</strong> At least 50 feet from where people are eating</li>
        <li><strong>Visible but not front-and-center:</strong> Guests should be able to find it easily</li>
        <li><strong>Level ground:</strong> Driveways work great. Grass is fine if level and firm.</li>
        <li><strong>Downwind:</strong> If there's a prevailing breeze, position it downwind from the party</li>
        <li><strong>Near the house but not too close:</strong> 30-75 feet from your back door is usually ideal</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Pro tip: If you want to hide it somewhat, you can set up a privacy screen or place it behind a shed or hedge.
      </p>

      <h2 id="timing">When to Schedule Delivery and Pickup</h2>

      <p>
        Here's what works best:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Delivery:</strong> Morning of the party, or the day before for peace of mind</li>
        <li><strong>Pickup:</strong> Day after the party (gives you a buffer)</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Most rental companies offer Friday delivery with Monday pickup for weekend parties - perfect for Saturday events.
      </p>

      <h2 id="graduation-parties">Special Considerations for Graduation Parties</h2>

      <p>
        Graduation parties are one of the most common reasons people rent porta potties. A few specific tips:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Open house format:</strong> If guests come and go over several hours, you might have more people at once than expected</li>
        <li><strong>Mixed ages:</strong> Consider an ADA-accessible unit for elderly grandparents</li>
        <li><strong>Photo opportunities:</strong> Keep the porta potty out of major photo zones</li>
        <li><strong>Timing:</strong> May and June are peak graduation season - book 2-3 weeks ahead</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="cost">What It'll Cost You</h2>

      <p>
        For a typical backyard party, expect:
      </p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8">
        <table class="min-w-full border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <thead class="bg-gray-50">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">Rental Type</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">Weekend Cost</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-900">Standard unit</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">$100 - $175</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-900">Deluxe with hand wash</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">$150 - $250</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-900">Flushable/VIP unit</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">$200 - $350</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-900">Delivery + pickup</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">Often included, or $50-100</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p>
        Split among party expenses (food, drinks, decorations), a porta potty is one of the more affordable additions that makes a real difference.
      </p>

      <h2 id="nice-touches">Nice Touches to Add</h2>

      <p>
        Want to make the porta potty experience more pleasant? Consider:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>A small sign:</strong> "Restrooms →" so guests don't have to ask</li>
        <li><strong>Solar path lights:</strong> If the party goes into evening</li>
        <li><strong>Hand sanitizer stand:</strong> Extra sanitizer near the exit</li>
        <li><strong>Air freshener:</strong> A clip-on freshener inside the unit</li>
        <li><strong>Extra toilet paper:</strong> Keep a roll in a waterproof container inside</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="common-concerns">Common Concerns (Addressed)</h2>

      <h3>"Will it smell?"</h3>
      <p>
        For a single-day event, no. Units are delivered freshly cleaned and serviced. Odors only become an issue with heavy use over multiple days without service.
      </p>

      <h3>"Will it look tacky?"</h3>
      <p>
        It's a porta potty, not a sculpture. But you can minimize visibility by placing it behind landscaping or adding a privacy screen. Some companies offer units in neutral colors instead of bright blue.
      </p>

      <h3>"What about my HOA?"</h3>
      <p>
        Check your HOA rules. Most allow temporary portable toilets for parties, but some require advance notice or limit how long they can stay.
      </p>

      <h3>"Do I need to do anything to prepare?"</h3>
      <p>
        Just have a clear, level spot for placement and make sure the delivery truck can access your property. The rental company handles setup.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
        <p class="font-semibold text-primary-800 mb-2">Planning a Backyard Party?</p>
        <p class="text-primary-700">
          Find porta potty providers in your area who specialize in event rentals.
          <a href="/services/weddings-parties" class="font-semibold underline">Browse party rental providers →</a>
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Related Posts -->
    <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Related Articles</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {relatedPosts.map((related) => (
          <a href={`/blog/${related.slug}`} class="group">
            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 h-full hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">
              <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide">{related.category}</span>
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-2 group-hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">{related.title}</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">{related.readTime}</p>
            </div>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Bottom Ad -->
    <div class="mt-8">
      <AdSlot slot="footer" />
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
